    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3088" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐμ-πί̄πτω</span></b> , aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔμπεσε</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">fall into</span> or
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">upon;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πῦρ ἔμπεσε νηυσίν,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 16.113</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> ἐν
            ὕ̄λῃ</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 11.155</span></i>; freq.
          in hostile sense, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔμπεσ᾽ ἐπικρατέως</span>,
          ‘charge,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 16.81</span></i>; metaph., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χόλος, δέος ἔμπεσε θῡμῷ,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 9.436</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 14.207</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> ἔπος μοι ἔμπεσε
            θῡμῷ</span>, ‘came to my mind,’ <i><span class="en">Od.
            12.266</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
